  <p id="image-caption"> Look at this cute goober</p>
  
  <h2>Origin</h2>
    <img id="sadgrub" src="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/hollowknight/images/0/0c/Grub.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/340?cb=20170417120822" alt id="sad grub">
  <p id="tribute-info"> These grubs are seen scattered in Hallownest - helplessly trapped in small glass jars. It's up to the Knight to rescue these poor creatures and reunite them with the Grubfather. In total there are 46 grubs to rescue. When you are near a grub it will make adorable sounds to indicate that it's nearby.  </p>
<iframe id="sounds" width="300" height="200" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/eGPI76PVjnw" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  <p id="listen"> Give them a listen!</p>
 
  <p id="cont"> When you rescue them, the Grubfather will give you rewards based on the amount you have saved. <a href="https://hollowknight.fandom.com/wiki/Grubfather#Rewards" style="color:#3a3e83;"target="_blank" id="tribute-link"> To see the rewards click here!</a></p>
    <img id="reward"src="https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/f/fc9bad07-819c-43d7-a770-aac5b07cca8f/de08gpj-850f8b28-85ca-4b75-9663-b1afbdf8e28c.gif?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ1cm46YXBwOiIsImlzcyI6InVybjphcHA6Iiwib2JqIjpbW3sicGF0aCI6IlwvZlwvZmM5YmFkMDctODE5Yy00M2Q3LWE3NzAtYWFjNWIwN2NjYThmXC9kZTA4Z3BqLTg1MGY4YjI4LTg1Y2EtNGI3NS05NjYzLWIxYWZiZGY4ZTI4Yy5naWYifV1dLCJhdWQiOlsidXJuOnNlcnZpY2U6ZmlsZS5kb3dubG9hZCJdfQ.qfoy47iyYnw5YdNGn0bNnXflcZatneEsHN9hRt6iO3k" alt id="Rewards from Grubfather">
    <p id="caption2"> Grubfather rewards Knight for saving 5 grubs</p>
    <h2> Why are they lost?</h2>
    <p id="cont">It's currently unknown why they were placed all over Hallownest and who is responsible. There are those that speculate a character called "The Collector" is responsible considering it had a map of all the grub locations - as well as an image of the Vitruvian Grub.</p>
<img id="collector"src="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/hollowknight/images/6/68/B_TheCollector.png/revision/latest?cb=20170412130603" alt id="Collector">
  <img id="map"src="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/hollowknight/images/5/53/Grub_Map.png/revision/latest?cb=20200321083037" alt id="Map of grub locations">
 <img id="art"src="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/hollowknight/images/8/88/Vitruvian_grub.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/340?cb=20180716212430" alt id="Vitruvian Grub">
    <p id="c1">The Collector</p>
    <p id="c2">Grub Map</p>
    <p id="c3">Vitruvian Grub</p>
    <p id="cont">For those that do believe the Collector is responsible for the grubs placement, it's believed it was to protect them from the Grubfather. Once all the grubs are collected, the GrubFather eats them but fear not! It's solely to help them with metamorphosis. This theory is based on the achievement for collecting all the grubs called "Metamorphosis". The charm given as reward is called "Grubberfly's Elegy", implying their final form will be reached by using the Grubfather as a coccoon.  </p>
  <img id="all" src="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/hollowknight/images/f/fd/Screenshot_HK_Grubfather_01.png/revision/latest?cb=20190227233144" alt id="All rescued grubs">
 <img id="grubfather"src="https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/hollowknight/images/2/2d/Screenshot_HK_Grubfather_03.png/revision/latest?cb=20191026135858"alt id="Grubs using Grubfather as coccoon">
    <p id="c4">All rescued grubs</p>
    <p id="c5">Grubfather with grubs inside him</p>
    <p id="cont"> As you adventure through Hallownest be sure to keep your eyes and ears out for these little critters. But be wary of mimics! They take the form of grubs but are actually monsters.</p>
<img id="mimic"src="https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/f/fc9bad07-819c-43d7-a770-aac5b07cca8f/de08lw2-659a65c6-f3e6-4d45-ba43-9ad90af4309d.gif?token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ1cm46YXBwOiIsImlzcyI6InVybjphcHA6Iiwib2JqIjpbW3sicGF0aCI6IlwvZlwvZmM5YmFkMDctODE5Yy00M2Q3LWE3NzAtYWFjNWIwN2NjYThmXC9kZTA4bHcyLTY1OWE2NWM2LWYzZTYtNGQ0NS1iYTQzLTlhZDkwYWY0MzA5ZC5naWYifV1dLCJhdWQiOlsidXJuOnNlcnZpY2U6ZmlsZS5kb3dubG9hZCJdfQ.AUbd1fJz8GkKcL4t7IjqE3eqApVmM6u8eBDPkbXabBE"alt id="Mimic grub">   
    <p id="c6">Encountering a mimic grub</p>
    <p id="cont"> Don't let these few mimics discourage you! The grubs need your help returning home safely - so let's save them!</p>
